iving-theory-test\" title=\"theory test\">theory test</a> <strong>before</strong> taking the motorcycle <a href=\"/motorcycle-practical-test\" title=\"practical test\">practical test</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can take the practical test on a motorcycle of between 75cc and 125cc.</p>\n\n<p>The licence you’ll get depends on the type of bike you take the test on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a light motorcycle licence (A1), which restricts you to ride bikes of up to 125cc and with a power output of 11kW</li>\n  <li>a standard motorcycle licence (A), if you take the test on a bike of over 120cc but not more than 125cc and capable of traveling at least 62mph</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you get the standard motorcycle licence you’ll be restricted for 2 years to riding bikes of up to 25kW power output and a power/weight ratio not exceeding 0.16kW/kg.</p>\n\n<p>After the 2 years you can then ride any size of bike.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’re 21 or over, or will reach 21 before this 2 year restriction ends, you have other options under the <a href=\"/ride-motorcycle-moped/direct-and-accelerated-access\" title=\"'direct access' and 'accelerated access' rules\">‘direct access’ and ‘accelerated access’ rules</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>More information</h2>\n\n<p>For further details download the DVLA&rsquo;s flowchart, which gives step-by-step instructions on how to get a moped or motorcycle licence.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@motor/documents/digitalasset/dg_198666.pdf\" title=\"download 'The routes to your motorcycle licence' (PDF, 90KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘The routes to your motorcycle licence’ (PDF, 90KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/ride-motorcycle-moped/direct-and-accelerated-access","slug":"direct-and-accelerated-access","order":2,"title":"Direct and accelerated access","body":"<p>You normally need to wait 2 years after passing your full motorcycle test before you can ride any size of bike.</p>\n\n<p>If you are 21 or over, or will reach 21 before the 2 years ends, you have other options.</p>\n\n<h2>Direct access</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re 21 or over when you take the motorcycle <a href=\"/motorcycle-practical-test\" title=\"practical test\">practical test</a>, and pass the test on a motorcycle with a power output of at least 35kW then you can ride any size of bike.</p>\n\n<p>You don’t need to have taken your Compulsory Basic Training (CBT) on a large bike (eg 40kW).</p>\n\n<h3>Rules for practising on a large bike</h3>\n\n<p>When you’re practising for the practical test on a bike that is larger than a standard learner bike you must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>be accompanied at all times by an approved direct access instructor on another bike and in radio contact</li>\n  <li>wear fluorescent or reflective clothing</li>\n  <li>follow all other provisional licence restrictions </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Accelerated access</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve passed the motorcycle <a href=\"/motorcycle-practical-test\" title=\"practical test\">practical test</a> but then reach 21 before the 2-year restriction period ends, you can take a further practical test for larger bikes of at least 35kW.</p>\n\n<h3>Rules for practising</h3>\n\n<p>You can practise on bikes over 25kW, but must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>be accompanied at all times by an approved instructor on another bike and in radio contact</li>\n  <li>wear fluorescent or reflective clothing</li>\n  <li>follow all other provisional licence restrictions </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>When you’re practising on a larger bike you will be classed as a learner rider.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you fail the test for a larger bike your existing motorcycle licence won’t be affected.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>The current rules will be replaced by new ones on 19 January 2013. The <a href=\"/ride-motorcycle-moped/new-rules-from-january-2013\" title=\"New rules for driving motorcycles and mopeds\">new rules</a> will affect you if you pass your test or apply to renew or replace your driving licence on or after this date.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/ride-motorcycle-moped/definitions-of-mopeds-and-different-motorcycles","slug":"definitions-of-mopeds-and-different-motorcycles","order":3,"title":"Definitions of mopeds and different motorcycles","body":"<h2>Mopeds</h2>\n\n<p>Mopeds have a maximum design speed not exceeding approximately 31mph. They have an engine size of up to 50cc.</p>\n\n<h2>Learner motorcycles</h2>\n\n<p>Learner motorcycles have an engine size of up to 125cc and a power output not exceeding 11kW.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>The current rules will be replaced by new ones on 19 January 2013. The <a href=\"/ride-motorcycle-moped/new-rules-from-january-2013\" title=\"New rules for driving motorcycles and mopeds\">new rules</a> will affect you if you pass your test or apply to renew or replace your driving licence on or after this date.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/ride-motorcycle-moped/minimum-ages-for-different-kinds-of-motorcycle-and-moped","slug":"minimum-ages-for-different-kinds-of-motorcycle-and-moped","order":4,"title":"Minimum ages for different kinds of motorcycle and moped","body":"<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Licence category</th>\n      <th>Type of vehicle</th>\n      <th>Minimum age</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>P</td>\n      <td>Mopeds with an engine size of up to 50cc and a maximum speed of up to approximately 31mph</td>\n      <td>16</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>A1</td>\n      <td>Light motorcycles with an engine size of up to 125cc and a power output of up to 11kW</td>\n      <td>17</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>A</td>\n      <td>Medium-sized motorcycles up to 25kW (33bhp) and a power to weight ratio of up to 0.16kW/kg</td>\n      <td